avro-c
------------------------------------------
Apache Avro(TM) is a data serialization system.

Avro provides:
 * Rich data structures.
 * A compact, fast, binary data format.
 * A container file, to store persistent data.
 * Remote procedure call (RPC).
 * Simple integration with dynamic languages. Code generation is not required
   to read or write data files nor to use or implement RPC protocols. Code
   generation as an optional optimization, only worth implementing for
   statically typed languages.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.6.0-1
  libavro-devel-1.8.1-1bl1
  libavro23.0.0-1.8.1-1bl1
  libjansson4-2.9-1bl1
  liblzma-devel-5.2.2-1
  liblzma5-5.2.2-1
  libsnappy1-1.1.3-1bl2
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1
  zlib-devel-1.2.8-3
  zlib0-1.2.8-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-4
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.22.0-1
  gcc-core-5.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-5.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://avro.apache.org/

Canonical download:
  http://ftp.tsukuba.wide.ad.jp/software/apache/avro/avro-1.8.1/c/avro-c-1.8.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack avro-c-1.8.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./avro-c-1.8.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/avro-c-1.8.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/avro-c-1.8.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libavro23.0.0-1.8.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libavro-devel-1.8.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

